t contribution to the known\npopulation in our own Galaxy. An observed higher density of sources in the\ndirection of the Magellanic Clouds can likely be explained by the relatively\nlow Galactic column density in their direction as well as a large number of\nexisting observations sensitive at low X-ray energies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Oct 2021 16:56:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-29"}
