s not unique, the shear flow pattern is observable up\nto time $1/A$. This provides a notion of stability despite the possible\nnon-uniqueness of the limit predicted by the convex integration theory. The\nresult relies on a new boundary vorticity estimate for the Navier-Stokes\nequation. This new estimate, inspired by previous work on higher regularity\nestimates for Navier-Stokes, provides a nonlinear control scalable through the\ninviscid limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Oct 2021 00:21:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Oct 2021 22:18:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 20:33:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-17"}
